WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.440
Hello everyone, today we are going to talk about a super important skill
大家好，今天我們要談論一項超級重要的技能

2
00:00:03.440 --> 00:00:06.080
How to communicate with your AI colleagues
如何與你的 AI 同事溝通

3
00:00:06.080 --> 00:00:08.840
That's right, you didn't hear wrong, it's a colleague
沒錯，你沒有聽錯，是同事

4
00:00:08.840 --> 00:00:13.240
Learn to give instructions is equivalent to mastering the key to working with this new partner
學會給出指示相當於掌握了與這個新夥伴工作的鑰匙

5
00:00:13.240 --> 00:00:15.360
Have you ever had this experience
你有過這種經歷嗎

6
00:00:15.360 --> 00:00:17.560
You think you've made it very clear
你認為你已經說得非常清楚了

7
00:00:17.560 --> 00:00:19.760
But that AI assistant
但那個 AI 助手

8
00:00:19.760 --> 00:00:22.840
I don't seem to understand what you're saying
似乎不理解你在說什麼

9
00:00:22.840 --> 00:00:25.040
It's really a little crazy, right?
真的有點令人抓狂，對吧？

10
00:00:25.040 --> 00:00:26.960
Don't worry, this is normal
別擔心，這很正常

11
00:00:26.960 --> 00:00:28.800
A lot of people are like you
很多人和你一樣

12
00:00:28.840 --> 00:00:30.160
What about the solution
那解決方案是什麼呢

13
00:00:30.160 --> 00:00:33.040
In fact, it's as expected
其實就像你想的那樣

14
00:00:33.040 --> 00:00:37.600
You imagine it as a new colleague who just reported
把它想像成一位剛剛入職的新同事

15
00:00:37.600 --> 00:00:40.240
He is super active and full of enthusiasm
他超級積極主動，充滿熱情

16
00:00:40.240 --> 00:00:41.960
I want to do things well
想把事情做好

17
00:00:41.960 --> 00:00:45.760
But he needs you to give him a very clear direction
但他需要你給他非常清晰的方向

18
00:00:45.760 --> 00:00:47.560
As long as you remember this core concept
只要你記住這個核心概念

19
00:00:47.560 --> 00:00:50.040
All the skills we're going to talk about later today
我們今天稍後要談的所有技能

20
00:00:50.040 --> 00:00:52.280
You will be able to communicate immediately
你就能立刻進行有效溝通

21
00:00:52.280 --> 00:00:53.760
Okay, let's get started
好的，讓我們開始吧

22
00:00:53.760 --> 00:00:58.200
Imagine today is your first day of work as an AI colleague
想像今天是你作為 AI 同事的第一天上班

23
00:00:58.200 --> 00:01:00.440
We will help him do a newbie training
我們將幫助他進行新手培訓

24
00:01:00.440 --> 00:01:04.640
Make sure we can work smoothly from the first day
確保我們從第一天就能順利合作

25
00:01:04.640 --> 00:01:07.920
OK, you may have heard a very powerful word
好的，你可能聽過一個非常厲害的詞

26
00:01:07.920 --> 00:01:11.920
It's called prompt engineering
叫做 prompt engineering（提示詞工程）

27
00:01:11.920 --> 00:01:13.880
Wow, it sounds like it's going to be written as a word
哇，聽起來好像要寫成一個詞

28
00:01:13.880 --> 00:01:15.240
It's complicated, right?
很複雜，對吧？

29
00:01:15.240 --> 00:01:16.280
But wait
但等等

30
00:01:16.280 --> 00:01:20.800
In fact, what we are talking about today is more like an effective communication skill
其實我們今天談論的更像是一種有效的溝通技能

31
00:01:20.800 --> 00:01:22.560
This really has nothing to do with writing
這真的和寫作無關

32
00:01:22.560 --> 00:01:27.280
The point is how you clearly and instinctively express your thoughts
重點是你如何清晰和直觀地表達你的想法

33
00:01:27.280 --> 00:01:30.640
It's exactly the same as you communicate with real people
這和你與真人溝通完全一樣

34
00:01:30.640 --> 00:01:35.200
Okay, next we're going to take a look at six super basic skills step by step
好的，接下來我們將逐步看六項超基礎的技能

35
00:01:35.200 --> 00:01:37.120
Really, as long as you master these six points
真的，只要你掌握這六點

36
00:01:37.120 --> 00:01:40.280
You will find that your communication quality with AI
你就會發現你與 AI 的溝通質量

37
00:01:40.280 --> 00:01:43.000
Wow, it's going to be a leap forward
哇，將會有飛躍性的提升

38
00:01:43.000 --> 00:01:45.160
Okay, let's get into the main topic
好的，讓我們進入主題

39
00:01:45.160 --> 00:01:50.360
This is like you want to handle the first project for that new colleague
這就像你想給那位新同事處理第一個項目

40
00:01:50.360 --> 00:01:54.880
The first step is to give a super clear task report
第一步是給出一份超級清晰的任務說明

41
00:01:54.880 --> 00:01:57.760
The first skill is also the most important
第一個技能也是最重要的

42
00:01:57.760 --> 00:02:00.520
Be sure to give the situation and purpose
一定要說明情況和目的

43
00:02:00.520 --> 00:02:03.400
You see, this comparison is super obvious
你看，這個對比非常明顯

44
00:02:03.400 --> 00:02:05.720
On the left, if you only say to AI
左邊，如果你只是對AI說

45
00:02:05.720 --> 00:02:08.000
Hey, tell me about climate change
嘿，告訴我關於氣候變遷的事

46
00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:09.440
Oh my god, the scope is so big
天哪，範圍太大了

47
00:02:09.440 --> 00:02:12.280
He can only guess what you want to know
它只能猜測你想知道什麼

48
00:02:12.280 --> 00:02:13.480
But look at the right
但看看右邊

49
00:02:13.480 --> 00:02:15.680
The instructions are completely different
指令完全不同

50
00:02:15.680 --> 00:02:20.280
He said I was preparing for a job interview for agricultural research in Indonesia
他說我在為印尼農業研究的工作面試做準備

51
00:02:20.320 --> 00:02:22.080
And then the specific requirements
然後是具體的要求

52
00:02:22.080 --> 00:02:26.280
Climate change has three main effects on tropical agriculture
氣候變遷對熱帶農業有三個主要影響

53
00:02:26.280 --> 00:02:27.480
You see, when you give this
你看，當你提供這些

54
00:02:27.480 --> 00:02:30.760
Why and where to use the background information
為什麼以及在哪裡使用背景信息

55
00:02:30.760 --> 00:02:33.880
The answer given by AI will be really accurate
AI給出的答案會非常準確

56
00:02:33.880 --> 00:02:35.400
And then the second skill
然後是第二個技能

57
00:02:35.400 --> 00:02:38.280
Define a role for AI
為AI定義一個角色

58
00:02:38.280 --> 00:02:40.680
This method is really, really super useful
這種方法真的、真的非常有用

59
00:02:40.680 --> 00:02:42.960
We call it the human color hint
我們稱之為人設提示

60
00:02:42.960 --> 00:02:46.240
You can directly specify that AI plays a certain expert
你可以直接指定AI扮演某位專家

61
00:02:46.240 --> 00:02:47.600
For example, you tell him
例如，你告訴它

62
00:02:47.600 --> 00:02:50.760
Please play an experienced science teacher
請扮演一位經驗豐富的科學老師

63
00:02:50.760 --> 00:02:52.840
Then use a smart 10-year-old child
然後用聰明的10歲小孩

64
00:02:52.840 --> 00:02:54.280
Also understand the method
也理解的方式

65
00:02:54.280 --> 00:02:57.080
Explain to me how the rainbow is formed
向我解釋彩虹是如何形成的

66
00:02:57.080 --> 00:02:59.040
Wow, you set it up like this
哇，你這樣設置

67
00:02:59.040 --> 00:03:02.520
The tone, use of words and the depth of explanation given by AI
AI提供的語氣、措辭和解釋深度

68
00:03:02.520 --> 00:03:04.280
Will be completely different
會完全不同

69
00:03:04.280 --> 00:03:06.240
Become super in place
變得非常恰當

70
00:03:06.240 --> 00:03:09.760
OK, we've set up the background and role
好的，我們設置了背景和角色

71
00:03:09.760 --> 00:03:11.200
What about the next step
下一步呢

72
00:03:11.200 --> 00:03:13.600
Of course, you have to tell him very specifically
當然，你必須很具體地告訴它

73
00:03:13.600 --> 00:03:14.880
The finished product you want
你想要的最終產品

74
00:03:14.880 --> 00:03:18.320
That is, what does the deliverable look like
也就是說，交付物看起來像什麼

75
00:03:18.320 --> 00:03:19.480
The third skill
第三個技能

76
00:03:19.480 --> 00:03:21.120
Do it directly for him
直接為它展示

77
00:03:21.120 --> 00:03:22.800
Don't just say it
不要只是說

78
00:03:22.800 --> 00:03:26.000
Well, as the saying goes, the voice is more important than the words
嗯，正如俗話所說，示範勝於言語

79
00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:27.440
Sometimes you give an example
有時候你給一個例子

80
00:03:27.440 --> 00:03:29.400
It's really more than a thousand words
真的勝過千言萬語

81
00:03:29.400 --> 00:03:32.240
This is called a few sample hint on a professional
這被稱為專業人士的少樣本提示

82
00:03:32.240 --> 00:03:33.440
It sounds great
聽起來很棒

83
00:03:33.440 --> 00:03:34.960
But the concept is very simple
但這個概念非常簡單

84
00:03:34.960 --> 00:03:36.640
Just like this example on the screen
就像屏幕上的這個例子

85
00:03:36.640 --> 00:03:40.080
You give him a sentence that is full of technical words before editing
你給它一個編輯前充滿技術詞彙的句子

86
00:03:40.080 --> 00:03:42.880
Then give him a modified version
然後給它一個修改過的版本

87
00:03:42.920 --> 00:03:44.160
AI just look
AI 只需要看看

88
00:03:44.160 --> 00:03:47.040
Oh, so this is the style you want
哦，所以這就是你想要的風格

89
00:03:47.040 --> 00:03:48.560
I'll learn it right away
我會立即學會

90
00:03:48.560 --> 00:03:49.680
The fourth skill
第四個技巧

91
00:03:49.680 --> 00:03:53.600
It is important to clearly specify the limit of output
清楚地指定輸出限制是很重要的

92
00:03:53.600 --> 00:03:55.360
For example, you can't just tell him
例如，你不能只告訴它

93
00:03:55.360 --> 00:03:56.640
Help me design a website
幫我設計一個網站

94
00:03:56.640 --> 00:03:57.960
It's too blurry
這太模糊了

95
00:03:57.960 --> 00:03:59.960
You have to give him specific conditions like this
你必須給它具體的條件，像這樣

96
00:03:59.960 --> 00:04:02.520
For example, the guide list must be fixed on top
例如，導航列必須固定在頂部

97
00:04:02.520 --> 00:04:04.440
The color should be the kind of sunset color
顏色應該是日落色那種

98
00:04:04.440 --> 00:04:07.400
And there should be a dark and light color mode to switch
而且應該有深色和淺色模式可以切換

99
00:04:07.400 --> 00:04:09.480
The clearer the frame you give
你給的框架越清楚

100
00:04:09.480 --> 00:04:10.680
What he does
它做出來的

101
00:04:10.720 --> 00:04:13.080
The more it will be the way you want
就越會是你想要的樣子

102
00:04:13.080 --> 00:04:14.720
Okay, the fifth skill
好的，第五個技巧

103
00:04:14.720 --> 00:04:18.320
Solve the complex tasks one by one
一個一個地解決複雜任務

104
00:04:18.320 --> 00:04:19.800
This method is also very famous
這個方法也很有名

105
00:04:19.800 --> 00:04:22.440
It's called a thought chain hint
它被稱為思維鏈提示

106
00:04:22.440 --> 00:04:24.680
Don't just throw a big question to him
不要只是把一個大問題扔給它

107
00:04:24.680 --> 00:04:27.240
Like helping me analyze the sales data of this season
像幫我分析本季的銷售數據

108
00:04:27.240 --> 00:04:29.200
So he might miss the focus
這樣它可能會偏離重點

109
00:04:29.200 --> 00:04:32.320
You can try to list your thinking process like this
你可以嘗試像這樣列出你的思考過程

110
00:04:32.320 --> 00:04:34.880
The first step is to find the best product
第一步是找出最好的產品

111
00:04:34.880 --> 00:04:36.920
The second step is to compare with the previous season
第二步是與上一季進行比較

112
00:04:36.920 --> 00:04:39.640
The third step is to find out which trends are very special
第三步是找出哪些趨勢非常特別

113
00:04:39.640 --> 00:04:41.920
The fourth step is to try to guess the reason
第四步是嘗試猜測原因

114
00:04:41.920 --> 00:04:44.320
You see, when you take him step by step
你看，當你一步步引導它

115
00:04:44.320 --> 00:04:45.920
He can follow your logic
它可以跟上你的邏輯

116
00:04:45.920 --> 00:04:48.440
The analysis report of output will of course be more in-depth
輸出的分析報告當然會更深入

117
00:04:48.440 --> 00:04:49.680
There are more regulations
還有更多規則

118
00:04:49.680 --> 00:04:50.280
Okay, here we go
好的，我們來吧

119
00:04:50.280 --> 00:04:52.080
Everyone must remember one key point
每個人都必須記住一個關鍵點

120
00:04:52.080 --> 00:04:53.200
Working with AI
與 AI 合作

121
00:04:53.200 --> 00:04:56.080
It's not a one-way guide that I say you do
這不是一種單向的指導，我說你做

122
00:04:56.080 --> 00:05:00.480
It's more like a process of coming back and forth, constantly communicating, constantly optimizing
這更像是一個不斷往返、持續溝通、不斷優化的過程

123
00:05:00.480 --> 00:05:02.720
This is also the fourth part we are going to enter
這也是我們即將進入的第四部分

124
00:05:02.720 --> 00:05:04.080
Cooperation
協作

125
00:05:04.080 --> 00:05:05.360
The sixth skill
第六個技能

126
00:05:05.360 --> 00:05:07.160
This is an advanced method
這是一個進階方法

127
00:05:07.160 --> 00:05:09.480
Is to ask him to think first
是要求它先思考

128
00:05:09.480 --> 00:05:10.280
It's wonderful, right?
很妙，對吧？

129
00:05:10.280 --> 00:05:13.440
You can add a sentence in front of your real instructions
你可以在實際指令前加一句話

130
00:05:13.440 --> 00:05:15.000
Like before answering
像在回答之前

131
00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:18.520
Please think about this question step by step
請逐步思考這個問題

132
00:05:18.520 --> 00:05:21.080
Describe all kinds of factors and possible restrictions
描述各種因素和可能的限制

133
00:05:21.080 --> 00:05:23.120
It's like you're telling your colleague
就像你在告訴你的同事

134
00:05:23.120 --> 00:05:24.400
Don't rush to do it
不要急著去做

135
00:05:24.400 --> 00:05:27.200
Take five minutes to think about the whole plan
花五分鐘思考整個計畫

136
00:05:27.200 --> 00:05:28.840
You give him the space to think
你給了它思考的空間

137
00:05:28.840 --> 00:05:32.120
The quality that is usually produced at the end will really be much better
最後通常產出的品質真的會好得多

138
00:05:32.120 --> 00:05:34.520
Okay, we just talked about six skills, right?
好的，我們剛才談到了六個技能，對吧？

139
00:05:34.520 --> 00:05:38.280
But if there is one of the most powerful and powerful
但如果有最強大、最有力的

140
00:05:38.280 --> 00:05:41.400
What do you think will be the ultimate skill?
你認為終極技能會是什麼？

141
00:05:41.400 --> 00:05:42.440
The answer is
答案是

142
00:05:42.440 --> 00:05:44.480
Our secret weapon is
我們的祕密武器是

143
00:05:44.480 --> 00:05:46.440
Please ask AI to help you
請要求 AI 幫助你

144
00:05:46.440 --> 00:05:47.000
That's right
沒錯

145
00:05:47.000 --> 00:05:49.520
When you are stuck and don't know how to give instructions
當你陷入困境，不知道如何下達指令

146
00:05:49.520 --> 00:05:51.120
You just tell him honestly
你只需要誠實地告訴它

147
00:05:51.120 --> 00:05:53.760
I'm not sure how to ask
我不確定該如何提問

148
00:05:53.760 --> 00:05:55.480
To get the best result
才能得到最好的結果

149
00:05:55.480 --> 00:05:56.800
You can help me
你能幫我嗎

150
00:05:56.800 --> 00:05:59.120
Design a better hint
設計一個更好的提示

151
00:05:59.120 --> 00:06:00.200
What will you do
你會做什麼

152
00:06:00.200 --> 00:06:01.960
The moment you ask this question
在你提出這個問題的那一刻

153
00:06:01.960 --> 00:06:03.760
AI uses an instruction tool
AI 使用指令工具

154
00:06:03.760 --> 00:06:07.280
Immediately upgraded to your personal advisor and assistant
立即升級成你的個人顧問和助手

155
00:06:07.280 --> 00:06:11.400
So the key is to constantly adjust and optimize
所以關鍵是不斷調整和優化

156
00:06:11.400 --> 00:06:12.720
The first result is not perfect
第一個結果並不完美

157
00:06:12.720 --> 00:06:14.320
That's super normal
那是非常正常的

158
00:06:14.320 --> 00:06:16.120
You can try these methods
你可以試試這些方法

159
00:06:16.120 --> 00:06:19.040
Tell him to give me three different styles of versions
告訴它給我三種不同風格的版本

160
00:06:19.040 --> 00:06:21.240
Or help me change the form
或幫我改變形式

161
00:06:21.240 --> 00:06:23.080
You can even challenge him and ask him
你甚至可以挑戰他，問他

162
00:06:23.080 --> 00:06:25.520
How much confidence do you have in your answer?
你對你的答案有多大的信心？

163
00:06:25.520 --> 00:06:27.200
Oh, by the way, there is a little skips
順便說一下，有個小技巧

164
00:06:27.200 --> 00:06:29.400
If you feel that the conversation is too strong
如果你覺得對話過於強烈

165
00:06:29.400 --> 00:06:32.040
Don't hesitate to start a new conversation directly
不要猶豫，直接開始新的對話

166
00:06:32.040 --> 00:06:33.800
Sometimes the effect is better
有時效果會更好

167
00:06:33.800 --> 00:06:35.960
Okay, let's sum it up
好的，讓我們總結一下

168
00:06:35.960 --> 00:06:36.800
You will find
你會發現

169
00:06:36.840 --> 00:06:38.120
What we learned today
我們今天學到的

170
00:06:38.120 --> 00:06:41.440
It's not just some tips to give instructions
不僅僅是一些指令技巧

171
00:06:41.440 --> 00:06:43.720
It's also a change of mentality
也是一種心態的改變

172
00:06:43.720 --> 00:06:45.880
That is, how can we become
也就是說，我們如何才能成為

173
00:06:45.880 --> 00:06:48.760
A better AI assistant
更好的 AI 助手

174
00:06:48.760 --> 00:06:49.600
This summary table
這個總結表格

175
00:06:49.600 --> 00:06:51.200
I think it's very well organized
我認為組織得非常好

176
00:06:51.200 --> 00:06:52.480
You can take a look
你可以看一看

177
00:06:52.480 --> 00:06:53.920
What to do
要做的事

178
00:06:53.920 --> 00:06:56.640
Is to give a clear task description
就是給出清晰的任務描述

179
00:06:56.640 --> 00:06:58.840
Provide a rich background
提供豐富的背景信息

180
00:06:58.840 --> 00:07:00.520
Don't do anything
不要做的事

181
00:07:00.520 --> 00:07:02.760
Just don't think that AI will read your mind
就是不要認為 AI 會讀心術

182
00:07:02.760 --> 00:07:05.120
Don't give that kind of blurry instruction
不要給出那種模糊不清的指令

183
00:07:05.120 --> 00:07:07.080
And please don't put a few
也請不要把幾個

184
00:07:07.080 --> 00:07:08.240
Irrelevant questions
無關的問題

185
00:07:08.240 --> 00:07:10.640
All mixed in the same dialogue
全部混在同一個對話中

186
00:07:10.640 --> 00:07:12.760
It's easy to mess it up
那很容易搞砸

187
00:07:12.760 --> 00:07:14.600
Finally, I want to leave a question
最後，我想留下一個問題

188
00:07:14.600 --> 00:07:16.560
Let's go back and think about it
讓我們回過頭去思考

189
00:07:16.560 --> 00:07:19.400
You see, the evolution of AI is so fast
你看，AI 的發展如此迅速

190
00:07:19.400 --> 00:07:21.840
In the future, we really need to spend more effort
在未來，我們確實需要花費更多精力

191
00:07:21.840 --> 00:07:24.160
To learn to adapt
來學習適應

192
00:07:24.160 --> 00:07:27.280
Is it a machine or are we human beings?
是機器還是我們人類？

193
00:07:27.280 --> 00:07:30.600
Maybe how to improve our own communication ability
也許如何提高我們自己的溝通能力

194
00:07:30.600 --> 00:07:35.080
Is the ultimate key to truly grasp the era of human-machine cooperation in the future
才是真正掌握未來人機協作時代的終極鑰匙
